theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A → closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hP3
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
    have h₁ : A ⊆ interior (closure A) := hP3
    have h₂ : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      fun x hx => subset_closure hx
    have hA : A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := fun x hx => h₂ (h₁ hx)
    exact closure_mono hA
  · -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
    have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h

theorem interior_inter_interior_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A B : Set X) :
    interior (A ∩ interior B) = interior A ∩ interior B := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    -- `x` lies in `A` and in `interior B`
    have hxAI : x ∈ A ∧ x ∈ interior B := (interior_subset : interior (A ∩ interior B) ⊆ _ ) hx
    rcases hx with ⟨U, hUo, hxU, hUSub⟩
    -- `U` witnesses that `x ∈ interior A`
    have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A := by
      refine ⟨U, hUo, hxU, ?_⟩
      intro y hy
      exact (hUSub hy).1
    exact And.intro hxIntA hxAI.2
  · rintro ⟨hxIntA, hxIntB⟩
    -- Obtain an open neighbourhood of `x` contained in `A`
    rcases hxIntA with ⟨U, hUo, hxU, hUSub⟩
    -- `interior B` is open and contains `x`
    have hVo : IsOpen (interior B) := isOpen_interior
    have hxV : x ∈ interior B := hxIntB
    -- Consider the intersection `W = U ∩ interior B`
    have hWo : IsOpen (U ∩ interior B) := hUo.inter hVo
    have hxW : x ∈ U ∩ interior B := And.intro hxU hxV
    have hWSub : (U ∩ interior B) ⊆ A ∩ interior B := by
      intro y hy
      exact And.intro (hUSub hy.1) hy.2
    exact ⟨U ∩ interior B, hWo, hxW, hWSub⟩

theorem interior_closure_union_interior_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (A ∪ interior A)) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, show that `A ∪ interior A = A`.
  have h_union : (A ∪ interior A : Set X) = A := by
    ext x
    constructor
    · intro hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hA => exact hA
      | inr hIntA => exact interior_subset hIntA
    · intro hx
      exact Or.inl hx
  -- Rewrite using the established equality.
  simpa [h_union]
